cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.GT, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with spectrum-power trading between a small cell and a macro cell, which involves optimizing the allocation of resources such as bandwidth and power. This falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper involves optimizing the allocation of resources while ensuring a minimum data rate requirement. This involves information theory concepts such as channel capacity and rate-distortion theory.
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with optimizing the energy efficiency of a system while ensuring quality of service requirements. This falls under the domain of systems and control.
4. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper involves optimizing the allocation of resources in a strategic setting where the small cell and macro cell engage in spectrum-power trading. This falls under the domain of game theory.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper involves optimizing the allocation of resources for serving macro cell users and small cell users, which may involve multimedia content such as video streaming. This falls under the domain of multimedia.
